entry.title: [Profile DragDrop] Add reaction to dragover not to miss any dragenter event
entry.content:
This CL fixes two issues:

- Entering a tile will cause it to shift, however the dragging tile can still stay 'within' the shifting tile. In that case we would expect the shifted tile to shift back, however since no new drag enter event is happening, it won't. Solution: Introduce the drag over reaction.

- Shifting tiles that are on the edge of rows, and shifting from different rows can cause unexpected drag enter events. We do not want to trigger drag enter/over at this stage (when a tile is shifting). Solution: introduce the shifting tag and prevent reactions.

entry.title: Disable UseAuthSessionStorage feature by default
entry.content:
AuthSessionStorage does intentionally not allow concurrent access to its

UserContext and crashes if there's already a user of the UserContext it

holds on to. The UseAuthSessionStorage feature replace the dependency of

AuthFactorConfig on QuickUnlockStorage with AuthSessionStorage. However,

AuthFactorConfig still assumes the UserContext ownership model of

QuickUnlockStorage, where the UserContext is always available (for valid

tokens), so there's a mismatch. This led to crash b/296192527, and

b/296195532 might also be related to this.

entry.title: Automatically annotate dangling ExperimentalAsh pointers [5/N]
entry.content:
This patch is:

- Automated. See [automation] section.

- Not affecting users, only Chrome's CQ. See [no-op] section.



This is a split affecting:

- extensions/



Context:

--------

@bartekn is going to remove the `ExperimentalAsh` raw_ptr annotation.

This was a performance experiment to enable/disable MiraclePtr on a

subset of new pointers added for ChromeOS ash (non-lacros).



Before removing it, he needs to enable it by default in code. Enabling

MiraclePtr for them, causes the DanglingPointerDetector to be enforced.

To pass the CQ, we need to annotate pre-existing dangling pointer with

`DanglingUntriaged`. After enabling ExperimentalAsh feature, it won't be

allowed anymore for those pointers to become dangling.



Automation:

-----------

1. Enable the `PartitionAllocBackupRefPtrForAsh` feature flag.

2. Apply the 'annotator' CL: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/4474553

3. Run all the gtests. See https://docs.google.com/document/d/1AMMERcqy0eafFWopUCHYsIKIKEp3J8DFxqW9UIbzIHo

4. Concatenate all the output_*, `filter`, `sort -nr`, `uniq`.

5. Run https://github.com/ArthurSonzogni/chrome-dangling-ptr-apply-edit

6. Run `git cl format`

7. Cherry-pick the patch created from (5)



no-op:

------

The DanglingPointerDetector is not enabled against users. It only

affects tests and chromium developers.

entry.title: Fix crash in CastOS touch selection tests.
entry.content:
According to [1], the touch selection menu is not supported on Cast so

no menu runner instance is created. This causes a crash in

TouchSelectionControllerImpl when it tries to show or hide the menu

using the runner instance (which then causes various touch selection

related tests to consistently fail on cast builders, e.g. [2]).



Fix this by modifying TouchSelectionControllerImpl to check whether the

menu runner is non-null before using it, and adjusting ui/views/BUILD.gn

so that the touch selection menu is not included for cast.



[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:ui/views/views_delegate.cc;l=36;drc=3e1a26c44c024d97dc9a4c09bbc6a2365398ca2c

entry.title: Implement MediaStreamVideoTrack deliverable frames counter.
entry.content:
In preparation for adding a MediaStreamTrack.getStats() API, update the

blink internal guts to count deliverable frames.



A deliverable frame is a frame that "either was delivered to a sink or

would have been delivered to a sink, if one was connected". In other

words, it is a frame that was neither dropped or discarded.



This does not include any frames while the track is muted (in which

case no frames are flowing, so no frames are counted) or disabled (in

which case the source frames are substituted by black frames and we

don't increment the counter).

entry.title: Implement MediaStreamVideoSource frame drop counters.
entry.content:
In preparation for adding a MediaStreamTrack.getStats() API, update the

blink internal guts to count dropped frames.



In this API, frames will either be considered delivered, discarded or

dropped. Delivered frames are those frames that did not result in a

discarded/dropped event and will be added in a follow-up CL.



This CL implements the discarded/dropped counters on

MediaStreamVideoSource, which is a parent class to all video sources.

This means that a) frame drops are counted even if the drop happened

before the frame reached the renderer process, since `OnFrameDropped`

is signalled via MOJO, and b) the frame counters will work regardless

of what type of track this is.

- ios/chrome/browser/photos/BUILD.gn

- ios/chrome/browser/photos/DEPS

- ios/chrome/browser/photos/photos_availability.h

- ios/chrome/browser/photos/photos_availability.mm

- ios/chrome/browser/ui/context_menu/BUILD.gn

This adds a function

```

bool IsSaveToPhotosAvailableForImageUrl(

const GURL& image_url, ChromeBrowserState* browser_state);

```

which returns whether the Save to Photos entry point can be presented

for a given image URL and browser state.



- ios/chrome/browser/shared/model/prefs/browser_prefs.mm

- ios/chrome/browser/shared/model/prefs/pref_names.h

- ios/chrome/browser/shared/model/prefs/pref_names.cc

A new unsynced string pref `kIosSaveToPhotosDefaultGaiaId` is registered

to memorize the Gaia ID of the account selected by the user in the Save

to Photos account picker if they unchecked "Ask every time".



- i/c/b/shared/public/commands/BUILD.gn

- i/c/b/shared/public/commands/save_image_to_photos_command.h

- i/c/b/shared/public/commands/save_image_to_photos_command.mm

- i/c/b/shared/public/commands/save_to_photos_commands.h

SaveToPhotosCommands is the command handler protocol for Save to Photos,

to be implemented by BrowserCoordinator. It contains two commands

```

- (void)saveImageToPhotos:(SaveImageToPhotosCommand*)command;

- (void)stopSaveToPhotos;

```

which respectively start and stop the Save to Photos feature.

`SaveImageToPhotosCommand` stores the data needed to configure the

SaveToPhotosCoordinator before it is started i.e. the image source URL,

its referrer and the web state it comes from.



- ios/chrome/browser/flags/about_flags.mm

- ios/chrome/browser/flags/ios_chrome_flag_descriptions.h

- ios/chrome/browser/flags/ios_chrome_flag_descriptions.cc

- ios/chrome/browser/shared/public/features/features.h

- ios/chrome/browser/shared/public/features/features.mm

This adds the Save to Photos feature flag to enable a Finch rollout.

entry.title: Stop duplicating HasManagedSyncDataType() in SetupList
entry.content:
The main goal of this CL is to address the TODO below.

HasManagedSyncDataType() is moved from ios/chrome/browser/ui/ to

ios/chrome/browser/sync/ so it can be invoked in the linked code path.

https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:ios/chrome/browser/ntp/set_up_list.h;l=19;drc=602d8a0907a60c346acca81ffef364cb0d276524



But: we'd have to move at least IsManagedSyncDataType() and

IsSyncDisabledByPolicy() from the same file for consistency. These are

thin wrappers around the public components/sync/ API, not worth the

indirection. So rather than move them, this CL inlines them. Note some

of the inlined sites don't need to null check SyncService because it's

already unconditionally dereferenced or CHECK-ed in the same class.



IsRestrictAccountsToPatternsEnabled() is left as is for now because

it doesn't fit under /sync/. I have other plans for it.

entry.content:

switch to camera B but it failed to open, then camera A will be opened

to be opened. This CL keeps the orders of devices sorted by preferred

facing and try the devices one by one.

entry.title: Transition to "Menlo" monospace font on Mac
entry.content:
We are using "Courier" as a default monospace font on Mac. Other

browsers, like FF and Safari are using "Menlo" font.



"Menlo" has a better glyph coverage compared to "Courier". It has glyphs

for box-drawing unicode characters and for cyrillic script while

"Courier" does not have them. It also has better glyph attachments

stacking for zalgo text [0].



Changed font sizes in web_tests/external/wpt/css/css-display/display-contents-shadow-dom-1.html and web_tests/external/wpt/css/css-multicol/multicol-width-ch-001.xht due to the pixel differences in glyphs' positions after the change. It was happening because of the rounding of glyphs positions' value (presumably because wpt tests are running without antialiasing and subpixel positioning), see https://bugs.chromium.org/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=1409445. "Menlo" has different advances from "Courier" that's why we wasn't facing this issue before. Changed tests are testing different logic and font size is not affecting that.



[0] https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zalgo_text

entry.title: [fetch-later] Implement fetchLater API's send-on-context-destroy behavior
entry.content:
This CL introduces `FetchManager::DeferredLoader`, which roughly maps

to a deferred fetch record[1] in Blink.



`FetchManager::Loader` is updated to allow subclass, and to not relying

on ScriptPromiseResolver to obtain `ScriptState`, as FetchLater API does

not support Promise.



Underlying, the DeferredLoader



- creates a ResourceRequest with a new flag `is_fetch_later_api` set to

true.

The flag is piped to network service, to be used in browser.

- does not handle any responses.

- get disposed on context destroyed, the same as Loader.



A DeferredLoader evetually leads to creation of an

content::KeepAliveURLLoader in browser (as its keepalive flag is also

true), which is updated to support deferred loading behavior with the

following extra methods:



- KeepAliveURLLoader::IsDeferred()

- KeepAliveURLLoader::StartDeferredLoad()



KeepAliveURLLoaderService uses the `is_fetch_later_api` flag to tell

whether a request should be handled by a deferred KeepAliveURLLoader.

If true, the request will only be started when the corresponding

mojom::URLLoader is disconnected from a renderer.



Design Doc: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1U8XSnICPY3j-fjzG35UVm6zjwL6LvX6ETU3T8WrzLyQ/edit



[1]: https://whatpr.org/fetch/1647/094ea69...152d725.html#deferred-fetch-record

entry.title: Settings: Fix "About Chrome" icon in sidenav to be visible in HCM.
entry.content:
The about chrome icon is drawn as an svg bitmask on a background. In

HCM, the background of the span is indistinguishable from the background

of the div behind it, rendering the icon invisible. This CL adds special

logic for HCM to use the ButtonText system color as the background

color. Note that this special logic cannot be moved to cr_icons.css

since the aboutIcon id specifies a background-color and takes precedence

over the .cr-icon class.

entry.content:
Attempting to synchronize an OzoneImageBacking between multiple

different write streams (e.g. SHARED_IMAGE_USAGE_DISPLAY_READ|

SHARED_IMAGE_USAGE_WEBGPU) where one specific driver implementation does

not support synchronizing with GpuFence (e.g. Dawn on Linux which

require opaque external fences instead of sync files) is guaranteed to

fail. Check for this in OzoneImageBacking::IsSupported to let those

cases fall back to supported SharedImageBacking implementations.

entry.title: [Extensions] Rename EventListenerParam to EventListenerOwner
entry.content:
mojom::EventListenerParam is a union that represents the owner of the

context in which a listener for an extension event is created. This may

not always be an extension, since extension events can also be used in

various web contexts (like the webstore or Chrome WebUI).



Rename this parameter to EventListenerOwner, which more accurately

conveys its intention (since there are many other parameters associated

with EventListeners).



This CL is a pure rename and has no behavior change.
